item.title: About Me
item.dc:creator: jessepiburngmailcom
item.content:encoded: My name is Jesse Piburn and I am a data scientist in the Computational Sciences and Engineering Division at Oak Ridge National Laboratory. I currently work in the Geographic Information Sciences and Technology Group focusing on geographic data science, spatio-temporal analytics, and machine learning. When not sending emails, I spend my time programming in R. I'm married to my wonderful wife, Ashley, and we are expecting our first child in November. Well that is if you don't count Charlie, our chocolate lab. Outside of work, I enjoy playing fantasy football, feeding ducks, and watching The Joy of Painting with Bob Ross. I am way too emotionally invested in the Tennessee Vols.
